// xhelix integrity baseline refresh on dpkg transactions.
//
// After every apt-get / dpkg upgrade or install, kick the daemon to
// re-hash the affected packages and refresh the baseline. This is the
// B2 → B1 feedback loop: when a legit package-manager transaction
// changes a binary, the baseline learns the new SHA so B3 (execve
// SHA check) doesn't fire false positives on the very next exec.
//
// Failure of this hook does NOT block the dpkg transaction — xhelix
// is best-effort. The daemon's B2 authentic-upgrade tester will catch
// the legit writer at execve time anyway.

DPkg::Post-Invoke {
  "if [ -x /usr/local/bin/xhelixctl ]; then /usr/local/bin/xhelixctl integrity refresh-recent --quiet 2>/dev/null || true; fi";
};
